title: Ground News - King County Announces $1 Million in Additional Support for Asylees and Refugees in Tukwila
text: King County Executive Dow Constantine has announced that King County will be providing an additional $1 million in emergency funding to support refugee families in Tukwila. After an application process that will run through March 12, the County will select one or more nonprofit organizations to contract with to provide temporary housing, food, support, and legal services.
